Do these git commands only if after doing step6 it generates dirty.opk :
make distclean
make clean
make mrproper
git pull
To generate kernel opk
1.	make -j4 ARCH=arm CROSS_COMPILE=/opt/tooling/codesourcery/MGC-2014.05-46-arm-gcc-4.8.3/Sourcery_CodeBench_for_ARM_Embedded/bin/arm-none-linux-gnueabi- imx_v6_v7_defconfig
It will generate the config file, modify config file :
1.	Vim .config

2.	uname –r on target to get kernel release version and then modify the .config file as mentioned below.
+ CONFIG_LOCALVERSION="-04317-g32fb2e5"
+ CONFIG_LOCALVERSION_AUTO=n
3.	vim scripts/setlocalversion
+ #               echo "+"
2.	make -j4 ARCH=arm CROSS_COMPILE=/opt/tooling/codesourcery/MGC-2014.05-46-arm-gcc-4.8.3/Sourcery_CodeBench_for_ARM_Embedded/bin/arm-none-linux-gnueabi- menuconfig
define zip format for uImage(gzip,lzzp etc..)

3.	make -j4 ARCH=arm CROSS_COMPILE=/opt/tooling/codesourcery/MGC-2014.05-46-arm-gcc-4.8.3/Sourcery_CodeBench_for_ARM_Embedded/bin/arm-none-linux-gnueabi- LOADADDR=0x10008000 uImage
Will create uImage: path will be mentioned if its success
4.	make -j4 ARCH=arm CROSS_COMPILE=/opt/tooling/codesourcery/MGC-2014.05-46-arm-gcc-4.8.3/Sourcery_CodeBench_for_ARM_Embedded/bin/arm-none-linux-gnueabi- modules
will create modules
5.	make -j4 ARCH=arm CROSS_COMPILE=/opt/tooling/codesourcery/MGC-2014.05-46-arm-gcc-4.8.3/Sourcery_CodeBench_for_ARM_Embedded/bin/arm-none-linux-gnueabi- dtbs
will create dtbs

6.	../scripts-bosch-gen3/opk/mkp.
Will generate below .opk
rbcm-linux-kernel_3.14.61-04317-g32fb2e5.opk
7.	Copy generated opk to target and install
scp rbcm-linux-kernel_3.14.61-04317-g32fb2e5.opk root@172.17.0.1:/tmp
opkg install /tmp/ rbcm-linux-kernel_3.14.61-04317-g32fb2e5.opk
reboot

If target panics:
1.	Check if uname –r[3.14.61-04317-g32fb2e5] name is same as what is in /lib/modules on target : if its different do below steps:
1.	After generating modules as above : create package of it 

make -j8 ARCH=arm CROSS_COMPILE=/opt/tooling/codesourcery/MGC-2014.05-46-arm-gcc-4.8.3/Sourcery_CodeBench_for_ARM_Embedded/bin/arm-none-linux-gnueabi- INSTALL_MOD_STRIP=1 modules_install INSTALL_MOD_PATH=~/temp

The 3.14.61-04317-g32fb2e5eb should be generated in /home/hsr9kor/temp/lib/modules/ on Ubuntu
Copy it on target at /lib/modules/
reboot
2.	If still reboot :
Copy module as above
Copy uImage following steps: [
https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/display/gen3generic/Target+kernel+update+via+opk ]
section: [Linux kernel image and device tree (eMMC => VW MiB, Suzuki, PSA, JAC etc)]

3.	If still reboot check if module is taken as older version as on target u have 2 versions now, then should remove older version in /lib/modules/ and keep only one “eb” in /lib/modules/ on target and do the step2 again.  


Debug kernel panics:
https://www.collabora.com/news-and-blog/blog/2016/06/10/linux-kernel-memory-corruption-debug-tricks/



